<p>Varley's results show that technical SEO is not separate from content growth. It enables it. When Google can crawl your site efficiently, your content gets indexed faster. When your pages load quickly, users stay longer. When your structured data is correct, you earn rich snippets that increase click-through rates.</p>
<h3>Key Lesson</h3>
<p>Before investing in content production, verify that your technical foundation can support it. A site with crawl errors, slow speeds, and broken redirects will not rank regardless of content quality. For ecommerce stores on complex platforms like headless Shopify or custom builds, a technical SEO audit should precede any content strategy.</p>
